@node "Overview" "LARP overview"
Well, not getting into detail. The goal of this program should be pretty
clear. And the goal - well it's to display little messages in a window. You
can enter these messages via @{"arexx" link "Arexx-interface" 0}.

The messages can be 78 chars long and the program holds currently a history of
60 messages by default. This can be altered by a @{"tooltype" link "Tooltype & CLI" 0} or a @{"CLI-parameter" link "Tooltype & CLI" 0}.
You can by resizing the window larger see the older messages. As a little
extra you can change the font which LARP is using for a cosmetic touch.
          
@endnode

@node "Arexx-interface" "LARP Arexx interface"
The name of the program's arexx-port(which is an application port - not
global) is LARP.01 or .02 and so on. It depends on if you have other LARPs
running. I have only implemented a couple of rexx commands. The most usable is
PUTS "<text here>". There's also SIZE '<x-size> <y-size> and PLACE
'<x-coordinate> <y-coordinate>. Could do lot's of other neat commands like
LOAD "<filename>" and so on but the goal in this project was speed(exactly
three hours took the first version).        
@endnode

@node "Tooltype & CLI" "LARP tooltypes & CLI-interface"
LARP can be configured using the tooltypes interface in Workbench and the
CLI-interface in shell. Both interfaces have the same capabilities.

Tooltypes:

PUBSCREEN       You can specify any public screen name in this
                tooltype. If this tooltype has been set, LARP tries to
                open its window on the screen in the tooltype. If it
                can't success, LARP will exit so make sure that your
                public screen is already open. If this tooltype hasn't
                been set then LARP tries to open its window on the
                default public screen which is usually the Workbench
                screen.

SYNOPSIS:       PUBSCREEN=<pubscreen name>

QUIET           By default LARP will drag your public screen to the
                front. With this tooltype you can make it not to drag
                it to the front. (This tooltype is usable only with
                PUBSCREEN-tooltype.)

SYNOPSIS:       QUIET=TRUE/FALSE

HISTORY         By default the amount of messages which LARP holds in
                the buffer is sixty. However you can change this with
                this tooltype.

SYNOPSIS:       HISTORY=<amount of messages in the buffer>

FONTNAME        If you like you can change the font which LARP uses
                with this tooltype.

SYNOPSIS:       FONTNAME=<name of the font>

FONTSIZE        With this tooltype you can change the size of the font
                which LARP uses. This can be used separately or with
                FONTNAME.

SYNOPSIS:       FONTSIZE=<size of the font>

CLI-interface:

CLI-interface has all the same parameters as tooltypes. You can enter
parameters in any order but they must be separated by a white space. Also the
CLI-interface differs in the way you enter "variables". Meaning that you must
replace '=' with ' '.    
@endnode

