@node "Bugs" "Bugs - well, sort of.."
Program eats exactly 40 bytes of memory every time it's run if you don't do
anything else than just start the program and exit. More memory will be eaten
if you send arexx commands to it. The reason to this is unknown to me. I would
very much like to hear if you find out the reason. The @{"Arexx" link "Arexx-interface" 0} memory eating
could be a fault of dice. Not sure though.

Program has a dummy way to handle the messages. Every message is considered to
be 80 bytes.

The way how LARP updates window is dummy. Making LARP slower. Howewer I found
the speed acceptable on a A1200.

(4.7.94) The memory eating is propably a fault of Designer. I used to do GUIs
for my programs with it. It works by making "ready" c-code. Allthough I've
modified it quite heavily - the same bug is in all programs(written by me)
which use Designer based code.

(4.7.94) A pretty weird bug haunted me in the development process of version
1.3 - If you start program from CLI - it will say Cannot open window... But if
you RUN(as the command) the program from CLI. It will work fine. At the end. I
got the machine to hang while debugging and when I tried again - it worked
just fine - so if you're experiensing these kinds of problems, don't hesitate
to contact.       
@endnode

@node "History" "History"
1.1     First public release.(2.7.94)

1.1a    Allocates mem dynamically - rather than just declares it. Also
        some little cleanup.(2.7.94)

1.2     Hmm - somewhat a breakthru this version. I've made numerous
        changes which don't see on the screen. But I've added a
        @{"tooltype" link "Tooltype & CLI" 0}: PUBSCREEN=<pubscreenname>. Also changed the name of
        the window to one in LARP-rev.h. This version hasn't been
        tested so much - so please email me for any bugs.(4.7.94)

1.3     Another bigger upgrade. Another tooltype: QUIET=TRUE/FALSE and
        @{"CLI interface" link "Tooltype & CLI" 0} were done.(4.7.94)

1.35    A couple more @{"Rexx commands" link "Arexx-interface" 0}: PLACE '<x-coordinate>
        <y-coordinate>' and SIZE '<x-size> <y-size>'.(7.7.94)

1.36    A few bug fixes: Didn't work properly with sysihack - fixed,
        made screen update a little more intelligent.(18.7.94)

1.38    Added the HISTORY=<amount of messages> and CLI-parameter.(19.7.94)

1.45    Numerous additions.. Added FONTNAME and FONTSIZE. This means
        that whole program is font sensitive. Also fixed few potential
        bugs.(20.7.94)  
@endnode

